      {/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */}
      {/* INTRODUCTION */}
      {/* ------------------------------------------------------------------ */}

      <p>
        Silverfish are one of the most common household insects in the United Kingdom, and yet they are among the least understood. If you have ever switched on the bathroom light at night and seen a small, silvery insect dart across the floor and vanish into a crack, you have almost certainly encountered a silverfish. While they are harmless to humans &mdash; they do not bite, sting, or carry disease &mdash; silverfish are a reliable indicator that your home has a humidity or damp problem, and in significant numbers they can cause real damage to books, documents, wallpaper, photographs, and clothing.
      </p>

      <p>
